diff --git a/bsp/m5stack_stopwatch/README.md b/bsp/m5stack_stopwatch/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..d586b74
--- /dev/null
+++ b/bsp/m5stack_stopwatch/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,89 @@
+# BSP: M5Stack StopWatch
+
+| Hardware | SoC | Component |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| [M5Stack StopWatch](https://docs.m5stack.com/en/core/StopWatch) | ESP32-S3 | `espressif/m5stack_stopwatch` |
+
+## Overview
+
+This BSP provides native ESP-IDF support for the M5Stack StopWatch. It does not depend on Arduino, M5Unified, or M5GFX at runtime.
+
+Supported onboard hardware:
+
+- 466 x 466 CO5300 AMOLED over QSPI, including controller brightness control
+- CST820B single-point touch on the shared I2C bus
+- two active-low physical buttons
+- ES8311 speaker and microphone through full-duplex I2S
+- BMI270 six-axis IMU through the sensor-hub API
+- M5PM1 power initialization, battery/input voltage, and power-source reporting
+- M5IOE1 display, touch, audio, speaker, USB/UART mux, and vibration control
+- RX8130CE address and shared-I2C access for applications that provide an RTC driver
+
+The CST820B uses the same address and coordinate register layout as CST816S. This BSP intentionally reuses the existing `esp_lcd_touch_cst816s` component; hardware validation of touch coordinates is part of the board acceptance test.
+
+## Basic display and touch
+
+```c
+#include "bsp/esp-bsp.h"
+
+lv_display_t *display = bsp_display_start();
+assert(display != NULL);
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(bsp_display_backlight_on());
+```
+
+The low-level display API is available through `bsp/display.h`. The logical display resolution is 466 x 466; the BSP applies the panel's required six-pixel X offset internally.
+
+## Audio
+
+The ES8311 is one bidirectional codec. Speaker and microphone initialization return the same `ESP_CODEC_DEV_TYPE_IN_OUT` handle, so an application should open it once for the sample format it uses.
+
+```c
+esp_codec_dev_handle_t codec = bsp_audio_codec_speaker_init();
+assert(codec != NULL);
+
+esp_codec_dev_sample_info_t format = {
+    .sample_rate = 44100,
+    .channel = 1,
+    .bits_per_sample = 16,
+};
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(esp_codec_dev_open(codec, &format));
+```
+
+## Buttons, IMU, power, and vibration
+
+```c
+button_handle_t buttons[BSP_BUTTON_NUM] = {0};
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(bsp_iot_button_create(buttons, NULL, BSP_BUTTON_NUM));
+
+uint16_t battery_mv;
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(bsp_stopwatch_get_battery_voltage(&battery_mv));
+
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(bsp_stopwatch_vibration_set(60));
+vTaskDelay(pdMS_TO_TICKS(100));
+ESP_ERROR_CHECK(bsp_stopwatch_vibration_set(0));
+```
+
+`bsp_stopwatch_vibration_set()` only changes PWM state and does not block. Timing a vibration pulse remains under application control.
+
+## Hardware notes
+
+| Function | Connection |
+| --- | --- |
+| Shared I2C | SDA GPIO47, SCL GPIO48 |
+| CO5300 QSPI | SCLK 40, D0 41, D1 42, D2 46, D3 45, CS 39, TE 38 |
+| Touch interrupt | GPIO13 |
+| ES8311 I2S | MCLK 18, BCLK 17, WS 15, DOUT 21, DIN 16 |
+| Buttons | A GPIO2, B GPIO1, active low |
+| RTC | RX8130CE at I2C address `0x32` |
+
+The M5IOE1 can appear at `0x4F` or `0x6F`; initialization probes both and `bsp_io_expander_get_address()` reports the detected address. The BSP does not expose an RX8130CE date/time API because no verified driver for that RTC exists in this repository.
+
+## Build
+
+From a compatible example directory:
+
+```powershell
+idf.py -B build.stopwatch -D SDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS=sdkconfig.bsp.m5stack_stopwatch build
+```
+
+The board requires ESP-IDF 5.4 or newer, 16 MB flash configuration, and an ESP32-S3 target.
diff --git a/bsp/m5stack_stopwatch/idf_component.yml b/bsp/m5stack_stopwatch/idf_component.yml
